Pediatric Care Africa (PCA) brought bundles of festive cheer to several children who were due to spend Christmas in the paediatric ward of Rob Ferreira Hospital.  Dressed as Father Christmas, complete with a big bag of presents, PCA’s founder, Dr André Hattingh, surprised the children with a visit and loads of goodies on the morning of December 24. ALSO READ: Dr Enos Mabuza Drive’s traffic lights remain out of order  Each of the children received a personalised gift and some sweet treats from PCA. Santa even gave some of the hospital nursing staff gifts.  Next on his itinerary were the children of Katoen near White River, who were positively delighted by his presents and presence.   